<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Low Tech Magazine Style Layout</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="page">
      <header class="masthead">
        <div class="meta-row">
          <span>Vol. 17 • Independent Edition</span>
          <span>Updated: March 2026</span>
        </div>
        <div class="brand">
          <div class="sun" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <div>
            <h1>Low-Tech Journal</h1>
            <p class="tagline">Doubts on progress and technology</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <nav>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
          <li><a href="#">Archive</a></li>
          <li><a href="#">Off-Grid Web</a></li>
          <li><a href="#">Long Reads</a></li>
          <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>

      <section class="layout">
        <section class="main">
          <article class="feature">
            <span class="label">Featured</span>
            <h2>The Return of Mechanical Cooling in an Overheated Digital Era</h2>
            <p>
              A practical look at resilient systems, low-energy material choices, and why constraints can improve design quality.
            </p>
            <div class="hero-img" aria-hidden="true"></div>
            <p>
              This layout is a visual recreation inspired by the tone of solar.lowtechmagazine.com, with warm newspaper colors,
              dense serif typography, and explicit section framing.
            </p>
          </article>

          <section class="list">
            <article class="post">
              <span class="label">Energy</span>
              <h3>Solar Websites and Seasonal Performance Limits</h3>
              <p>Designing publishing schedules around daylight, weather, and battery constraints.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="post">
              <span class="label">Materials</span>
              <h3>How to Build Durable Interfaces with Fewer Layers</h3>
              <p>Reduction as a strategy for maintenance, speed, and long-term compatibility.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="post">
              <span class="label">History</span>
              <h3>Infrastructure Before Abundance</h3>
              <p>What pre-electrification systems can teach modern software teams.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="post">
              <span class="label">Practice</span>
              <h3>Cold Storage, Paper Archives, and Slow Access Patterns</h3>
              <p>When slower systems increase reliability and reduce total cost.</p>
            </article>
          </section>
        </section>

        <aside class="side">
          <section class="panel">
            <h4>Latest</h4>
            <div class="body">
              <ul>
                <li>Off-grid publication checklist</li>
                <li>Seasonal reader traffic report</li>
                <li>Archive scan quality improvements</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="panel">
            <h4>Newsletter</h4>
            <div class="body">
              Monthly dispatch on low-energy technology and design constraints.
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="panel">
            <h4>Support</h4>
            <div class="body">
              Reader-funded, ad-free, and intentionally small.
            </div>
          </section>
        </aside>
      </section>

      <footer>
        <span>Recreation for learning purposes</span>
        <span>Built with plain HTML + CSS</span>
      </footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
